# ==============================================================================
# .dvcignore — SpectraMind V50 (NeurIPS 2025 Ariel Data Challenge)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose:
# • Prevent DVC from scanning ephemeral / reproducible files, caches, CI outputs
# • Speed up `dvc status` / `dvc repro` by scoping to true data/model artifacts
# • Keep Git, Docker, Kaggle, Hydra, and ML ecosystem ignores aligned
# • Ensure secrets and transient outputs are never versioned by DVC
#
# Notes:
# • .dvcignore affects what DVC scans; it does NOT affect Git.
# • Track datasets/models explicitly via `dvc add` (do not blanket-ignore their roots).
# • Keep this in logical sync with: .gitignore, .dockerignore
# ==============================================================================

